-- U.S. mortgage applications dips in latest week-MBA
-- By Caroline Valetkevitch
-- Wed Oct 01, 2014 07:00AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Oct 1 (Reuters) - Applications for U.S. home mortgages slipped last week, while interest rates also fell, an industry group said on Wednesday.

The Mortgage Bankers Association said its seasonally adjusted index of mortgage application activity, which includes both refinancing and home purchase demand, fell 0.2 percent in the week ended Sept. 26. The MBA's seasonally adjusted index of refinancing applications fell 0.3 percent, while the gauge of loan requests for home purchases, a leading indicator of home sales, were unchanged.  <^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ U.S. mortgage data: http://link.reuters.com/guv37s ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^> Fixed 30-year mortgage rates averaged 4.33 percent in the week, down 6 basis points from 4.39 percent the week before.